flowRoot.flowPara: Complete a breif set of questions about your background and diagnosis, and we will match you with upcoming studies at the University of Virginia and emerging resources throughout the state. Together we can find new ways to improve the lives of people living with Autism.
We have worked to carefully currate resoures available in Virginia for people on the Autism Spectrum. You can search for the resources here.
When you join the registry we will be able to notify you when enrollment opens for studies that may benefit you.
These are resources recently added to our registry. We will continue to add this list over time. We will notify registered participants about resources of interest.

flowRoot.flowPara: By joining the Registry, we will be able to let you know about resources and upcoming events in your community. We can also match you with research opportunities that might be a good fit for you and your family. Your participation will help us learn more about autism so we can create new solutions to achieve positive outcomes.

We will ask you to answer some questions about yourself or your family member with autism. We will use this information to provide you with the most relevant information about resources and upcoming studies. These questions should take about 10-15 minutes. If you don’t finish all the questions at once, you can save your progress and return later. You can also come back and modify your information or cancel your account at any time.
